        <p>Hi,</p>

<p>On: <a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.auth.adapter.openid.html">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a></p>

<p>The example contains the following:</p>

<p>if (!$result-&gt;isValid()) {
        $status = "You are logged-in as " . $auth-&gt;getIdentity() . "<br />\n";
    } else {
        $auth-&gt;clearIdentity();
        foreach ($result-&gt;getMessages() as $message) {
            $status .= "$message<br />\n";
        }
    }</p>

<p>However this has a negation in the wrong place. To work it need to be:</p>

<p>if ($result-&gt;isValid()) {
        $status = "You are logged-in as " . $auth-&gt;getIdentity() . "<br />\n";
    } else {
        $auth-&gt;clearIdentity();
        foreach ($result-&gt;getMessages() as $message) {
            $status .= "$message<br />\n";
        }
    }</p>

<p>Note removal of ! in outer if statement.</p>

